subSubSection.paragraph:
Eurycarcinus orientalis
is so far reported from the Gulf of Aden, Persian Gulf, Gulf of Oman , Pakistan , India , and Thailand ( Naderloo, 2017 ;
Ng et al. , 2018
). In India , the species is recorded from Gujarat , Maharashtra , Karnataka ( Chhapgar, 1957 ) and Kerala ( Dev Roy, 2013 ).
Trivedi et al. (2018)
commented that all the records of this species from the east coast including Andhra Pradesh ( Dev Roy and Nandi, 2007 ), Orissa ( Dev Roy and Rath, 2017 ), West Bengal ( Dev Roy and Nandi, 2012 ), and Andaman and Nicobar Islands ( Dev Roy and Nandi, 2012 ) require re-examination.

